shirley  ‘the haunting of hill house’ signed first edition second print£ shirley jackson  ‘the haunting of hill house’ signed and inscribed first edition second printing printed before publication published by the viking press ny in the us inscribed on the front free end paper ffep “for sean soan or som with love shirley october ” perhaps a fan send her the book to inscribe and being unable to decipher the person’s handwriting jackson penned the aforementioned inscription condition very good plus in a very good dust jacket the book is free from any previous owners’ inscriptions the board are clean the page block edges are clean slight fading of the yellow colour to a small area at the top of the spine the dust jacket is not price clipped has a few short tears and small area of loss to the top of the spine otherwise in very good condition signed copies are exceptionally scarce due to the reclusiveness of shirley jackson which was fuelled by her husband we recommend ruth franklins’s biography “shirley jackson – a rather haunted life’ for an interesting read consequently signed first printing copies would fetch several thousand at auctions our price represents fair value factoring in that this is a second printing it is also noteworthy that the second print run was commissioned before publications raising the question why the publishers has not commissioned a larger first printing to begin with shirley died in  at the tender age of  ‘the haunting of hill house’ is considered one of the best ghost stories ever written her work has had a huge influence on the likes of stephen king neil gaiman and richard matheson – terrific writers in their own right out of stock categories crime  thrillers fantasy landmark books literary fiction additional information reviews  additional information weight  kg reviews there are no reviews yet be the first to review “jackson shirley  ‘the haunting of hill house’ signed first edition second print” cancel reply your email address will not 