 as a consultant in semiconductor theory to att bell laboratories in murray hill nj dr jackson was appointed as commissioner of the nuclear regulatory commission as chair in  her many awards include memberships candace award national coalition of  black women mit educational council  to present the board of trustees for lincoln university  to present the nuclear regulatory commission and the national academy of sciences from  sigma xi delta sigma theta the american academy of arts and sciences aaas and the new york academy of sciences on july   the honorable dr shirley ann jackson became the th president of rensselaer polytechnic institute dr jackson is married to dr morris a washington also a physicist the family has one son alan a graduate of dartmouth college reference rensselaer polytechnic institute rpi  th st troy ny    to be a biophysicist to become an astrophysicist person  name  jackson dr shirley related videos  science career advice jamice obianyo jamice obianyo of ecolab talks about the broader benefits of a science education   average select ratingcancel ratingpoorokaygoodgreatawesome your rating none average   votes average select ratingcancel ratingpoorokaygoodgreatawesome your rating none average   votes stats  views login to favorite science  medicine science medicine the registry by categories activist  abolitionist business education episode filmtv literature music politicslawmilitary religion science medicine sportsoutdoors theatrethe arts today in american history black architecture still standing the shotgun house activist john hope had a vision tanner ame church an arizona home for blacks valaida snow a phenomental entertainer dorothy west a renaissance woman the harlem hell fighters commissioned charlie sifford born cornel west an orator of an intelligent soul patrice johnson born another black man killed by the police freddy adu the natural of soccer view all home search online community see  hear donate get involved resources the registry c